            "title": "Description",
            "answer": "<p></p><p><strong>Brighten & rejuvenate your eyes with Red Light & EMS technology</strong><br/><br/>Introducing Acid Eclipse™ DermaGlow Glasses; a cutting-edge, at-home treatment designed to reduce the appearance of under-eye bags and puffiness, brighten dark circles, smooth fine lines, and soothe the delicate skin around the eyes. Clinically backed red light and EMS technology work together to not only target visible signs of ageing, but also help calm eczema-related irritation, dryness, and redness often triggered by hormonal changes, all in just 5-20 minutes, five times a week.<br/><strong><br/>The science of youthful eyes</strong><br/><br/>Our DermaGlow glasses combine two powerful technologies:<br/><br/><strong>Red & Infrared Light Therapy: </strong>Penetrates deep into the skin to stimulate collagen production, improve circulation, and reduce discoloration, making under-eyes appear brighter and whilst firming sagging skin.<br/><br/><strong>EMS (Electronic Muscle Stimulation) Microcurrents: </strong>Targets sagging skin by using electrical currents to gently contract the orbicularis oculi (eye muscles), helping to firm, lift, and depuff the under-eye area for a more sculpted appearance.<br/><br/>With two EMS modes (constant & pulse) and three intensity levels, you can customise your treatment based on your skin’s needs and the severity of your eye bags, wrinkles and dark circles.<br/><br/><strong>Your at-home under-eye solution</strong><br/><br/><strong>Two powerful therapies in one device: </strong>Red and infrared light therapy helps reduce dark circles, fine lines and puffiness, while EMS microcurrents work to lift & tighten.<br/><br/><strong>Customisable & comfortable:</strong> Choose from two EMS modes (constant or pulse) and three intensity levels to find the perfect setting for your skin.<br/><br/><strong>Visible results with consistent use:</strong> Most users see a difference in as little as two weeks, with continued improvements over time.<br/><br/><strong>Cordless & rechargeable: </strong>Designed for convenience, the lightweight, wireless design lets you use it anywhere, anytime without the need for a power outlet.<br/><br/><strong>Gentle yet effective: </strong>Treatments are non-invasive & pain-free, making this the perfect addition to your daily skincare routine regardless of your skin type or sensitivity level.<br/><br/><em>Experience brighter, smoother & more awake looking eyes<br/></em><br/>With consistent use (5-20 minutes, five times a week), the Acid Eclipse™ DermaGlow Glasses are your at-home solution for reducing eye bags, dark circles, and fine lines and improving the health of dry, red flaky skin, often triggered by hormonal changes like perimenopause - no needles, no downtime, just results.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_ibXPy8": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "LED Wavelengths",
            "answer": "<p></p><p><strong>Red light (640nm) </strong><br/>Three wavelengths in one, your go-to for all things fine lines and sagging. Boosts collagen production and visibly reduces fine line depth for a firmer, younger-looking complexion.</p><p><strong>Near-Infrared light (840nm)</strong><br/>Penetrates deeper layers of the skin than red light to enhance circulation, reduce inflammation, and accelerate wound healing. Supports tissue repair and is ideal for calming rosacea and eczema symptoms.</p><p><strong>Deep Near-Infrared light (1072nm)</strong><br/>The deepest-penetrating wavelength, clinically shown to stimulate fibroblast (skin cell) activity for intensive collagen and elastin renewal. Helps firm sagging skin, reduce wrinkles at a structural level, and relieve muscular tension in the face and jaw.<br/><br/><strong>Blue light (415nm)</strong><br/>Targets acne and blemishes by neutralising bacteria, leaving your skin clearer and smoother.<br/><br/><strong>Green light (525nm)</strong><br/>Targets inflamed blood vessels beneath the skin to even out skin tone and fade discoloration for a more balanced, radiant complexion. The most effective LED for reducing the appearance of Rosacea.<br/><strong><br/>Purple light (405nm)</strong><br/>Combines red and blue light benefits to stimulate collagen production whilst attacking blemishes to improve skin texture and promote a revitalised appearance.<br/><br/><strong>Yellow light (590nm)</strong><br/><em>[Our founder's favourite setting] </em>Soothes sensitive skin and reduces redness, unveiling brighter, bouncier skin.<br/><br/><strong>White light (600nm)</strong><br/>Penetrates deep into the skin to promote cell regeneration, helping to smooth texture and improve skin health over time. Best for treating stubborn eczema and aids in visible reduction of Rosacea alongside green light. <br/><br/><strong>Cyan light (500nm)</strong><br/>Combines blue and green light to target both breakouts and uneven skin tone, reducing pore congestion while promoting a more radiant look.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_KyeTi4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How to use",
            "answer": "<p></p><p><strong>1 - Cleanse Your Face:</strong> Start with a freshly cleansed, makeup-free face.</p><p><strong>2 - Select a Light Mode:</strong> Using the DermaGlow remote, choose the LED mode that best suits your skin needs. </p><p><strong>3 - Secure the Mask:</strong> Position the mask over your face and neck and secure with the velcro straps.</p><p><strong>4 - The Session:</strong> Press the power button to start your treatment - remove once the 5-minute treatment is over. </p><p><strong>5 - Finish Up:</strong> Remove the mask and continue with your regular skincare routine.</p><p><em>For best results, finish your skincare routine and moisturiser after treatment.</em></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_dhQ476": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How often to use",
            "answer": "<p></p><p>For best results, our in-house dermatologists recommend using the DermaGlow 3–6 times per week.</p><p>We recommend everyone, even regular LED therapy users, follow these recommendations. </p><p>In your first week, begin with 3 sessions per week. This allows your skin to adjust to the powerful medical-grade LEDs.</p><p>Once your skin has adjusted and is responding well, increase the number of weekly treatments to up to 6 sessions per week. </p><p>We always recommend a minimum of 1 day per week where we allow the skin to rest fully.</p>"
          }
        },
